article.headline: Jacksonville St. 95, Reinhardt 72
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- With 23 points, Courtney Bradley led the Jacksonville State Gamecocks to a 95-72 victory over Reinhardt. The Gamecocks (1-2) shot 50 percent from the floor and led the Eagles (6-4) by 18 points at halftime. Nick Smith and Erik Adams added to Jacksonville's score with 14 points each, and Will Ginn chipped in with 13 points and eight assists. Brenden Slotter led the Eagles with 18 points, followed by Victor Stowes with 17 points and Carl Williams with 12 points and eight rebounds. Reinhardt had 26 points in the paint, while Jacksonville had more than twice that with 54.
